# 8. たしかな一歩

Minori: I-Is it time yet...?!
Shizuku: If that notice was correct, then it should be up soon...
Saito: I-I-I-It's up! The commercial's up on Gran Fleur's official channel!
Saito: I-I-I'll hit the play button now...
Haruka: Your hands are shaking so much, Saito...
Airi: Honestly... You and Haruka already checked over the footage, right?
Saito: Y-Yes, but this is a completely different situation. That time, I watched it as this group's manager... That's totally different from getting to watch it as a fan as it releases...!
Minori: I know exactly how you feel, Saito! Let's get ourselves mentally prepared by taking some deep breaths!
Saito: Thank you for understanding, Minori...!
Minori & Saito: *Inhale* *Exhale*
Saito: Alright...! Here we go...!
Shizuku: <Make your eyes more radiant.>
Yu: <Capture their attention, and never let go.>
Shizuku & Yu: <Be overwhelmingly brilliant with the new Floraison Eclat line of colors.>
Shizuku & Yu: <Gran Fleur.>
Minori: O-O-Oh...
Minori: Woooooow! Sh-Sh-Sh-Sh-Sh-She's so beautiful!!!
Minori: Wh-Wh-Wh-Wh-What do I do...?! I want to express how pretty Shizuku looks, but I'm struggling to find the right words...!
Airi: Same... She's also left me totally speechless...!
Airi: Still, she really did look gorgeous.
Minori: Yeah!! Thank goodness this commercial turned out so amazingly well...!!
Minori: Wait a second... Where'd Saito go?
Airi: Why are you bawling your eyes out?!
Saito: B-Because Shizuku looked so divine...!
Saito: *Sob* I'm so glad to be alive right now... This is the last thing I want to see before I depart this world...
Airi: You like it that much?!
Minori: N-No, Saito, we need you to live a long, healthy life!
Saito: Yes...! I shall live alongside Shizuku, and go to the grave with her...!
Haruka: Hehe. It may be a little while before she stops crying.
Haruka: But this was pretty incredible... I really couldn't take my eyes off of you. I felt totally overwhelmed.
Shizuku: Hehe. Now I'm starting to feel a little embarrassed.
Minori: No, you deserve to be showered with even more praise! That close-up in particular was just a beauty overload!
Saito: Oh, look here...! People are already posting tons of comments about this commercial.
Airi: Look at that. Everyone's going gaga for Shizuku.
Minori: “She's the elixir of life,” and, “The fairest of them all.” “I feel rejuvenated after seeing Shizuku's beauty.” Yes, these people get it!
Haruka: It's even getting a lot of traction on social media. If this keeps up, it might make it into the trending section.
Haruka: Oh...
Haruka: Look at this, Shizuku.
Shizuku: Huh?
Haruka: “Shizuku's in a different idol group now?” “I wanna see MORE MORE JUMP! Do a commercial together next!” “When's the next time they're gonna be on TV...?”
Haruka: Everyone's talking about MORE MORE JUMP! now because of you, Shizuku.
Shizuku: ...!
Saito: Shizuku made sure to mention MORE MORE JUMP! during the making-of video and interview for this commercial, so I have a feeling we'll be seeing more comments like these soon.
Shizuku: Thank goodness... I hope this leads to us receiving more offers for work...
Haruka: It may not happen immediately... But if this many people are already talking about us, then we should be able to turn our current situation around.
Haruka: Because their voices carry a lot of weight.
Airi: Right... At the very least, we should be able to knock something loose.
Airi: And we have you to thank, Shizuku!
Shizuku: Me...?
Minori: Yeah! Because you worked really, really hard for all of us!
Minori: Thank you so much, Shizuku!
Shizuku: You're welcome...!
Shizuku: (I'm so glad that I decided to take on this challenge.)
Shizuku: (I've been able to help the others...)
Shizuku: (And regain a very important piece of myself, which got lost somewhere along the way.)
Shizuku: (I'm prepared to carry everyone forward and keep shining as brightly as I can.)
Shizuku: (I'm not about to let that feeling go.)
Shizuku: (I need to keep getting better and better...)
Shizuku: (For the sake of our group's future...!!)
